Here's a JavaScript function that uses regex to extract a three-character code from a filename in the specified format:

```javascript
function extractThreeCharacterCode(filename) {
  const regex = /(\w{3})\.usfm$/;
  return filename.match(regex)[1];
}

// Usage example:
const inputFilename = '57-1Jn.usfm';
const extractedCode = extractThreeCharacterCode(inputFilename);
console.log(extractedCode); // Output: "1Jn"
```

This function searches the filename using the provided regex pattern, `(\w{3})\.usfm$`. It matches three alphanumeric characters (upper or lower case letters or digits) followed by a dot and ".usfm". The parentheses capture the three-character code as a group, and the `[1]` after `match(regex)` retrieves this group from the match result. If the filename does not match the expected format, the function will return `undefined`.
